HIGH|internal/ghaction/render.go:57|ghaction.Conclusion is a second, divergent merge-gate implementation. The canonical gate reconcile.IsFailing (internal/reconcile/gate.go:96-98) excludes findings whose Category is "out-of-scope" and that exclusion takes precedence over any verdict; atcr reconcile gates on it via CountAtOrAbove (cmd/atcr/reconcile.go:168). Conclusion only checks isRefuted + AtOrAbove(f.Severity, failOn) and never inspects f.Category, so an out-of-scope finding at/above the threshold FAILS the atcr github check while atcr reconcile passes it — the same review yields two opposite merge verdicts, undermining AC2's gate.|Replace the hand-rolled loop in Conclusion with a per-finding call to reconcile.IsFailing(f.Severity, f.Category, f.Verification, failOn, false) so the Action gate cannot diverge from the canonical gate. Verify with a finding {severity:CRITICAL, category:out-of-scope} and --fail-on CRITICAL: expect success, currently failure.|correctness|60|internal/ghaction/render.go:57-74|claude
MEDIUM|internal/ghaction/render.go:48|isRefuted compares with strings.EqualFold(f.Verification.Verdict, VerdictRefuted) — case-insensitive but no whitespace trim — whereas the canonical refuted check (internal/reconcile/disagree.go:206,210) routes the verdict through canonVerdict (ToLower+TrimSpace). A verdict with surrounding whitespace from an externally produced findings.json slips past EqualFold and is counted as blocking. Same divergence-from-canonical root as the Conclusion gate.|Normalize before comparing, e.g. strings.EqualFold(strings.TrimSpace(f.Verification.Verdict), VerdictRefuted), or reuse the reconcile canonicalizer. Verify with Verdict:" refuted ": must be treated as refuted and excluded.|correctness|15|internal/ghaction/render.go:48-50|claude
MEDIUM|internal/ghaction/render.go:79|cell() neutralizes only pipe and newline characters for table grammar, not markdown structure. f.Problem/f.Confidence (LLM-reviewer output) render into the check-run markdown table a maintainer reads; a problem string containing markdown links, extra pipes-as-text already handled, or fabricated table rows via markdown can spoof the audit surface. GitHub sanitizes raw HTML/JS so this is content-spoofing, not XSS, but still misleads the reader.|Escape or inline-code-fence cell content (wrap each value in a backtick span after escaping embedded backticks) so findings text renders inert. Verify a finding whose Problem contains a markdown link and a fake "| CRITICAL |" row renders as literal text.|security|60|internal/ghaction/render.go:79-85|claude
MEDIUM|internal/ghaction/render.go:114|BuildCheckOutput is exported and calls reconcile.ParseSeverity(failOn) discarding the error (threshold, _ := ...). When failOn is non-empty but invalid, the title branch runs, ParseSeverity returns ("", err), and the title becomes "atcr — N finding(s), 0 at/above " with an empty threshold; Conclusion separately returns "success" because AtOrAbove is false for an unknown threshold — an invalid threshold silently degrades to a malformed-title pass instead of an error. runGithub validates failOn but the exported function does not.|Document BuildCheckOutput as requiring a pre-validated canonical failOn, or surface/handle the parse error and render the raw failOn when parse fails. Verify BuildCheckOutput(findings, "bogus") title.|correctness|30|internal/ghaction/render.go:111-116|claude
MEDIUM|internal/ghaction/comments.go:30|BuildInlineComments skips a finding only when File is empty or Line<=0 (comments.go:33); it never checks Problem. A finding with File/Line set but Problem=="" yields commentBody output "ATCR found: ." (comments.go:52) — a posted, content-free inline PR comment. There is no lower bound on body content.|In BuildInlineComments also skip findings whose trimmed Problem is empty (or have commentBody return "" and skip empties in the caller). Verify with {file:a.go, line:5, problem:""}: no comment produced.|error-handling|15|internal/ghaction/comments.go:30-44|claude
MEDIUM|cmd/atcr/github.go:166|postInlineComments treats posted==0 && failed>0 as a systemic error and exits 1, but the documented benign case (a 422 for a finding whose line is not in the PR diff) breaks this at small N: a review with exactly one anchorable finding that legitimately 422s off-diff fails CI, the precise case the function comment says must not fail the run.|Inspect the client error status code: treat 422/unprocessable (off-diff) as expected/skipped and only fail on systemic auth/permission errors (401/403) dominating. Verify with one off-diff finding: run should succeed "0 posted, 1 skipped", not exit 1.|error-handling|60|cmd/atcr/github.go:155-170|claude
MEDIUM|internal/ghaction/client.go:98|post() treats every non-2xx identically as a terminal error with no retry/backoff. GitHub returns 429/403 with Retry-After for secondary rate limits and transient 502/503; with inline-comments enabled postInlineComments loops one POST per finding (cmd/atcr/github.go:157), so a large finding set can trip secondary rate limits and every subsequent comment fails, converting a transient throttle into "all comments failed → exit 1". No Retry-After/backoff handling exists in the package.|Add minimal retry-with-backoff honoring Retry-After / x-ratelimit-reset for 429/403-rate-limit and 5xx in post(), capped at a few attempts within the context deadline; at minimum distinguish rate-limit responses from genuine 4xx.|error-handling|120|internal/ghaction/client.go:92-102|claude
MEDIUM|action.yml:28|Required GitHub permissions (checks:write and, for inline comments, pull-requests:write) are documented only in the one-line github-token input description. A composite action cannot declare permissions:; a consumer who omits permissions:{checks:write} gets a late runtime 403 from the atcr github step with no early signal.|Document the required permissions: block prominently (docs + a comment at top of runs:) and/or add a preflight that fails fast with a clear "missing checks:write" message instead of relying on the API 403 surfacing late.|maintainability|30|action.yml:28-31|claude
LOW|internal/ghaction/render.go:131|The findings table renders cell(f.Severity) and cell(f.Confidence) verbatim with no normalization, while the gate (Conclusion/AtOrAbove) normalizes severity internally. A finding with severity:"critical" (lowercase) or " HIGH" displays un-normalized in the table while still counting toward the gate, so the displayed Severity column and the gate's effective severity can visually disagree.|Normalize severity via the same canonicalizer the gate uses (reconcile.ParseSeverity best-effort) before rendering the cell. Verify a severity:"critical" finding displays as CRITICAL.|maintainability|15|internal/ghaction/render.go:129-131|claude
LOW|internal/ghaction/render.go:33|FixAttribution reimplements the executor evidence-token grammar by splitting on "; " and CutPrefix("fix by "), duplicating internal/verify/executor.go serialization across a package boundary with no shared constant for the "; " separator. Any change to the executor join format silently breaks this consumer with no compile-time link.|Export the evidence join/parse from the producing package (internal/verify or reconcile) and have both sides use it, or at least share the "; " separator constant. Verify FixAttribution against the exact strings executor_test.go emits.|maintainability|30|internal/ghaction/render.go:24-43|claude
