LOW|action.yml:99|PR_NUMBER is set from github.event.pull_request.number, empty on non-pull_request triggers. With INLINE=true on such a trigger, --pr "" reaches the pr<=0 guard (cmd/atcr/github.go:93) and fails as a usage error (exit 2) — safe, but with a generic "requires --pr" message rather than a clear "inline-comments requires a pull_request event" diagnosis.|Guard INLINE=true against an empty PR_NUMBER in the action shell and emit an explicit error, mirroring the HEAD_SHA fallback pattern (action.yml:93-95), or document the constraint.|error-handling|15|action.yml:99-107|claude

